Ordering API Reference

Each ServiceStack Route will be listed with it's Return Type, which Verbs (aka Methods) are allowed to be used with it, the url path for the endpoint, notes entered by the developer in the code, a summary of the purpose of the endpoint, the data that the endpoint can take in (parameters) as well as the Return Type's properties (if an object model) and an example of how to call it in TypeScript.

AddPaymentToSalesOrder
PATCH | Returns: CEFActionResponse | Path: /Ordering/SalesOrder/AddPayment

Take payment information from the customer and perform an Authorize and/or Capture from the Payment Provider. If the total of all payments is less than the Balance Due, the status will be set to'Partial Payment Received', otherwise 'Full Payment Received'. An email notification will be sent to the customer.

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
ID int body Yes Not Set!
Payment PaymentModel body Yes The Payment information. This will only be Authorized and not Captured with the Payment Provider

TypeScript Example

var dto = <api.AddPaymentToSalesOrderDto>{
	ID: this.someValue1, // number 
	Payment: this.someValue2, // PaymentModel 
};
this.cvApi.ordering.AddPaymentToSalesOrder(dto).then(r => {
	if (!r || !r.data) {
		// Error State
		return;
	}
	this.something = r.data;
}).catch(reason => console.error(reason));

BackorderSalesOrder
PATCH | Returns: CEFActionResponse | Path: /Ordering/SalesOrder/Backorder/{ID}

The order items do not have sufficient stock. The order status will be set to 'Backordered'. An email notification will be sent to the customer. A Purchase Order should be created and reference this order by an Inventory Manager to refill stock.

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
ID int path Yes The identifier for the record to call.

TypeScript Example

var id: number = this.someValue1;
this.cvApi.ordering.BackorderSalesOrder(id).then(r => {
	if (!r || !r.data) {
		// Error State
		return;
	}
	this.something = r.data;
}).catch(reason => console.error(reason));

CapturePaymentForSalesOrder
PATCH | Returns: CEFActionResponse | Path: /Ordering/SalesOrder/CapturePayment/{ID}

Captures a pre-authorized payment on the order. No status change will occur.

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
ID int path Yes The identifier for the record to call.

VoidSalesOrder
PATCH | Returns: CEFActionResponse | Path: /Ordering/SalesOrder/Void/{ID}

Void the order. It will no longer be processed and will be visible on the Completed Orders view. An email notification will be sent to the customer.

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
ID int path Yes The identifier for the record to call.

		// Error State
		return;
	}
	this.something = r.data;
}).catch(reason => console.error(reason));
